						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and is dated the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Jaya.</hi> It refers itself to the reign of the Chāḷukya king <hi rend="bold">Āhavamalla</hi> and mentions a gift made by him. The king cannot be identified.</p>						

						<p>1. This inscription is engraved in continuation of No. 201.</p>						

